<p>To Theo van Gogh. The Hague, Tuesday, 2 May 1882.</p>
                    </vg:letContents>
<note type="sourceStatus" xml:id="sourceStatus">
<p>Original manuscript</p>
                    </note>
<note type="location" xml:id="location">
<p>Amsterdam, Van Gogh Museum, inv. no. b218 V/1962</p>
                    </note>
<note type="date" xml:id="date">
<p>Postmarked: Tuesday, 2 May 1882; this concurs with the comment below the signature: ‘Tuesday evening’.</p>
                    </note>
<note type="additionalDetail" xml:id="additionalDetail">
<p>Postcard (5 cents). Postmark: ‘’SGRAVENHAGE 7-8 N / 2 MEI 82’. It is addressed to ‘Monsieur Th. van Gogh./ 25 Rue de Laval./ <hi rend="ital">Paris.</hi>’ Van Gogh presumably wrote in English to make it difficult for others to read; cf. in this respect <ref target="let233.xml">letter 233</ref>.</p>
